@startuml
title Sprint 3 - Fluxo Cliente, Backend REST e Polling - HubArena

actor Cliente
participant "App Flutter\nCliente" as App
participant "ApiService" as Api
participant "Backend Flask\nREST" as Backend
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "RabbitMQ\nMOM" as MOM
actor "Postman / Prestador" as Prestador

Cliente -> App: Abre tela inicial
App -> Api: getCourts()
Api -> Backend: GET /courts
Backend -> DB: Consulta quadras
DB --> Backend: Lista de quadras
Backend --> Api: JSON
Api --> App: Lista de Court
App --> Cliente: Exibe quadras disponíveis

Cliente -> App: Seleciona quadra
App --> Cliente: Exibe detalhes

Cliente -> App: Cria reserva
App -> Api: createReservation()
Api -> Backend: POST /reservations
Backend -> DB: Salva reserva PENDING
Backend -> MOM: Publica evento reservation.created
Backend --> Api: Reserva criada
Api --> App: Reserva PENDING
App --> Cliente: Exibe reserva pendente

loop Polling a cada 5 segundos
  App -> Api: getReservations()
  Api -> Backend: GET /reservations
  Backend -> DB: Consulta reservas
  DB --> Backend: Lista de reservas
  Backend --> Api: JSON
  Api --> App: Reservas atualizadas
end

Prestador -> Backend: PUT /reservations/{id}/accept
Backend -> DB: Atualiza status ACCEPTED
Backend -> MOM: Publica evento reservation.accepted

App --> Cliente: Atualiza status para ACEITA automaticamente

@enduml
